pageContext.claim: “And unemployment in the United States has just reached the lowest level in over 51 years, and very soon, we think that will be broken to be a historic number.”
pageContext.analysis: The unemployment rate in the months before this speech was 3.6 percent to 3.7 percent, the best in  nearly 50 years, but well off the record 2.5 percent set in 1953.
